
STACK OPERATIONS – TIME & SPACE COMPLEXITY

Stack (LIFO) implemented using Linked List or Array

Operations:

  Top
   ↓
  [30] <- Node / Array element at top
  [20]
  [10]

1️⃣ Push
   - Description: Insert element at top
   - Diagram:
       Before: Top -> 20 -> 10
       After : Top -> 30 -> 20 -> 10
   - Time Complexity: O(1)
   - Space Complexity: O(1)

2️⃣ Pop
   - Description: Remove top element
   - Diagram:
       Before: Top -> 30 -> 20 -> 10
       After : Top -> 20 -> 10
   - Time Complexity: O(1)
   - Space Complexity: O(1)

3️⃣ Peek
   - Description: View top element
   - Diagram:
       Top element = 30
   - Time Complexity: O(1)
   - Space Complexity: O(1)

4️⃣ IsEmpty
   - Description: Check if stack is empty
   - Time Complexity: O(1)
   - Space Complexity: O(1)

5️⃣ Size
   - Description: Get number of elements
   - Time Complexity: O(1)
   - Space Complexity: O(1)

6️⃣ Display
   - Description: Print all elements from top to bottom
   - Diagram:
       Top -> 30 -> 20 -> 10
   - Time Complexity: O(n)
   - Space Complexity: O(1)



/*
STACK OPERATIONS – TIME & SPACE COMPLEXITY TABLE

+-----------+-------------------------------+-----------------+------------------+
| Operation | Description                   | Time Complexity | Space Complexity |
+-----------+-------------------------------+-----------------+------------------+
| Push      | Insert element at top         | O(1)            | O(1)             |
| Pop       | Remove element from top       | O(1)            | O(1)             |
| Peek     | View top element               | O(1)            | O(1)             |
| IsEmpty  | Check if stack is empty        | O(1)            | O(1)             |
| Size     | Get number of elements         | O(1)            | O(1)             |
| Display  | Print all elements             | O(n)            | O(1)             |
+-----------+-------------------------------+-----------------+------------------+

Notes:
- Stack follows LIFO (Last In First Out)
- All operations except Display work on the top element
*/